parameters.name: DhcpOptionsSetId
parameters.description: The ID of the DHCP options set. You can specify at most 20 IDs.

parameters.name: DhcpOptionsSetName
parameters.description:
The name of the DHCP options set.

The name must be 1 to 128 characters in length and can contain digits, underscores (\_), and hyphens (-). It must start with a letter.

Valid values:

 
*   tf-testAccVpcDhcpOptionsSets-1585169790614573448
 
    <!-- -->
 
    :
 
    <!-- -->
 
    tf-testAccVpcDhcpOptionsSets-1585169790614573448
 
    <!-- -->
 
    .

parameters.name: DomainName
parameters.description:
The root domain. For example, you can set the value to example.com.

After a DHCP options set is associated with a virtual private cloud (VPC), the root domain in the DHCP options set is automatically synchronized with the ECS instances in the VPC.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The number of entries per page. Valid values: **1** to **100**. Default value: **10**.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description:
The pagination token that is used in the next request to retrieve a new page of results. Valid values:

*   You do not need to specify this parameter for the first request.

*   You must specify the token that is obtained from the previous query as the value of the **NextToken** parameter.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description:
The region ID of the DHCP options sets that you want to query.

You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~36063~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: ResourceGroupId
parameters.description: The ID of the resource group to which the DHCP options set belongs.
